                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/217</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>202. With reference to Legation’s No. 440 of December 30, the War Trade Board are
                    unanimous in their feeling that the proposal to <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName> of December 20 is
                    eminently fair and reasonable and must stand.</p>
                <p>Referring to Legation’s No. 445 of January 3, the proposal of December 20 to
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName> itself
                    contains the best statement of the attitude and demands of United States and
                    needs no amplification <pb facs="0276" n="1110" xml:id="pg_1110"/> or
                    discussion, and you are instructed to publish full text of this proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
